<p>Viewing work packages by work flow state</p><p>Quickly view all work packages within a work flow state. 
  </p> 
	  
		<p> Within the 
		  Dashboard, the 
		  Workflow Time Line provides you with a visual
		  display of work packages in a specific work flow state. The work packages are
		  displayed as balls and are shown by date due and percentage complete. Using the
		  filters, you can change the view based on release, iteration, work flow,
		  resource, due date, or status. 
		 
	 </p> 
	  
		 
		   Select your product from the drop-down at the top of the
			 Dashboard tab. 
		   
		   
			 <p>The Dashboard is refreshed and
				shows status information for the selected product. 
			 </p> 
		   
		 
		   
		   
		 
		 
		   Scroll down to the 
			 Workflow Time Line. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Display the work flow state you want to see by using the filters,
			 display options, or navigation arrows. 
		   
		   
			 <p>The graph is refreshed and
				shows the work packages associated with the selected work flow state. The work
				packages are mapped on the graph based on due date and percentage complete. 
			 </p> 
		   
		  
		<p> The work flow state is displayed
		  with the associated work packages. 
		</p> 
	  
  